ht/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Grit Beneath the Glitter is the first real look at the new Las Vegas from the inside. In it, long-time residents as well as professionals reflect on the transformation of one of the fastest-growing and most famous cities on earth, yet one about which relatively little is known. They offer a lively and compelling portrait of the other side of Las Vegas: the people and institutions that support the glitter of the gaming and entertainment industry. Examining a range of topics--from the city's commercial history, labor conditions, and environmental problems to an analysis of the famous lights of the Strip--the contributors uncover the contradictions between the illusion and the reality of the city, the seam between fantasy and the life it masks. The essays in this collection explore the world that employees experience when they enter gaming palaces from an employee entrance in a back parking lot rather than through the scripted doors of casino/hotel palaces. They take readers into the neighborhoods where 1.4 million Americans now live, attend school, eat dinner, and go to work.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / West (AK, CA, CO, HI, ID, MT, NV, UT, WY).2bisacsh1 aDavis, Mike, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRothman, Hal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520935457423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520935457.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook